688.body:
Please provide valid PR description with example variable values.

The typically all-variable templates, especially in host names, are giving DNS provider very little information about what the template can do therefore being less secure than a template with more specific information. See sections "Variables and Host/Name in Template" and 'Variables and Security" in the spec.
Very often this is also an indicator, that there is not enough understanding of how templates work, especially when it comes to host processing.

## Pull Request Overview

This PR adds a Domain Connect template for HeyJamie AI's email service configuration. The template automates DNS record setup for their custom domain connector, including DKIM authentication, SPF records, and bounce handling.

Key changes:
- Creates a new Domain Connect template for HeyJamie AI email service
- Configures two variable TXT records for DKIM and SPF
- Adds a fixed CNAME record for bounce handling

14.body: In principle these changes look fine. However there is one problem.  Both templates have the same service id.  You need to distinguish these.  They can have the same serviceName, but the serviceId is used in the URLs to apply the correct template.
